# ── WHAT WAS BUILT (N4 deliverables, complete) ──────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. CONSTRAINED-SELECTION MECHANISM (host-side, on top of the existing forward):
#    tests/test_diffjudge_native.c. After diffusion_gemma_forward_cuda produces canvas
#    logits [n_tok x V], at the first canvas position (row P, the diffusion answer slot)
#    a HARD logit mask keeps ONLY the allowed token set {candidate tag tokens} U {NULL
#    token}; argmax over that subspace -> selected candidate (or NULL). Pure deterministic
#    argmax, no temperature/top-k/top-p. No change to cuda_forward.cu's compute is needed:
#    masking is a host scan of the allowed ids in the returned logits row.
#
#    TAG TOKENIZATION SOLVED (verified live against the .sp-tokenizer):
#      - gemma4 SPM auto-prepends BOS (id 2), so a "single-token" surface is one that,
#        after dropping a leading BOS, leaves exactly one content id. Probe confirmed
#        47 single-token tags available (need K=12). e.g. "AA"->[BOS,8686], "DD"->[BOS,21738].
#      - Each tag carries BOTH forms: BARE (the token inside "[TAG]", e.g. 8686) and
#        SPACE-PREFIXED (how the model writes it after a space, e.g. " AA"->23952). The
#        mask allows EITHER; both map to the same candidate slot (the model may emit
#        either the bracket-bare or the space-led token). NULL surface "NONE": bare=53212,
#        spaced=96869. vocab=262144.
#
# 2. JUDGE HARNESS (model resident, loops the corpus):
#    Loads the 26B model ONCE (arena mmap), then for each of the 90 matched primary
#    queries (bounded window K=12 = true needle + 11 random distractors, position-
#    shuffled, seed 20260621 == oracle) + 50 foreign (K random needles, no truth),
#    builds the tag-tight judge prompt (mirrors the PR-24423 JUDGE_TMPL), tokenizes
#    [prompt|canvas], runs ONE forward, applies the constrained argmax, records the pick.
#    Scores recall@1 (matched) + foreign-reject. Model stays resident across all queries.
#    Arch-gated on DIFFUSION_GEMMA, additive, default-off; dense gemma4 path byte-identical.
#    CMake target test_diffjudge_native added (tests/CMakeLists.txt). Built clean (no warnings).
#
# 3. The harness reached steady state correctly up to the forward call:
#      # single-token tags available=47 (need K=12)
#      # NULL surface='NONE' bare=53212 spaced=96869  vocab=262144
#      # loaded: V=262144 dg_canvas_length=256 (using CL=256)
#      # trial 1: P=367 n_tok=623 logits=653MB forward...
#    ...then BLOCKS inside diffusion_gemma_forward_cuda.
#
# ── THE BLOCKER (precise, reproducible) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# diffusion_gemma_forward_cuda deadlocks MID-TRAVERSAL with EVERYTHING IDLE:
#   - process CPU delta ~0.03-0.08s per 10s (essentially zero)
#   - GPU utilization 0%, GPU memory at the desktop baseline (~995 MiB; the forward's
#     small early device allocs happened, no kernel is running)
#   - PhysicalDisk %active ~0.05% (NOT paging — and C: is NVMe at 3032 MB/s raw read)
#   - process WorkingSet pinned at ~96-99 MB while "streaming" a 14 GB mmap
#   - OS file cache only ~369 MB, 19.7 GB RAM free
#
# REPRODUCES IN THE BASELINE: test_diffgemma_forward.exe (ctest G_DG_N1B) — NOT N4-specific.
# The forward IS structurally correct: with env-gated trace (SP_DG_TRACE=1, added as 16
# additive default-off DGDBG lines in cuda_forward.cu) it executes layers correctly when
# their weight pages happen to be warm, e.g.:
#   [dgtrace] layer 12: router downloaded, dispatching experts (NE=128 NU=8)
#   [dgtrace] layer 12: expert 19 cnt=258 dequant+gemm
#   [dgtrace] layer 12 done
#   [dgtrace] layer 13 done ...
# but then HANGS at the FIRST cold operation of a later layer. The stall layer is
# NONDETERMINISTIC across runs (observed stalls at L5, L12, L14) — it is the page-cache
# boundary, not a data-dependent bug at a fixed layer.
#
# With CUDA_LAUNCH_BLOCKING=1 (fully serialized) it still hangs, narrowed to:
#   [dgtrace] layer 5: router downloaded, dispatching experts (NE=128 NU=8)
#   [dgtrace] layer 5: expert 0 cnt=254 dequant+gemm   <-- hangs here, 0 CPU/GPU/disk
# i.e. inside the per-expert path dg_upload_arena_rows -> sp_arena_dequant_row, which
# reads OK_Q4B expert-weight rows through the CreateFileMapping/MapViewOfFile view of the
# 14 GB .sp-model (sp_model_load.c:59-61). The fault to bring those cold pages resident
# does not progress (disk idle, WS not growing) and the host thread never returns.
#
# Independently confirmed NOT a general GPU/driver/cublas fault:
#   - test_cuda_smoke.exe         -> PASS (sm_75 detected)
#   - test_moe_parity_cuda.exe    -> PASS (same gemm()/MoE kernels, expert-select identical,
#                                    rel-err 3.2e-07) — cublas + the MoE compute path are fine.
# Windows System event log shows NO TDR / nvlddmkm / display-driver-timeout events.
#
# ── DIAGNOSIS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The hang is in the native forward's COLD mmap-demand-paged weight streaming of the
# 14 GB model (CreateFileMapping/MapViewOfFile + per-row sp_arena_dequant_row), not in
# the N4 selection logic and not in GPU compute. The G_DG_N1B "GREEN" was recorded in a
# prior session (commit ce06ec6) when the model pages were evidently warm; on a cold
# mapping this build hangs nondeterministically before completing a single full forward.
# Because each judge query needs a full forward, the gate cannot run until the forward's
# weight-streaming hang is fixed.
#
# ── NEXT (to unblock the gate) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The fix is in the forward's weight-residency path, not N4:
#   (a) PRE-FAULT / pre-read the whole arena once after load (sequential touch of the
#       mapped view, or PrefetchVirtualMemory) so the per-row faults during the forward
#       hit resident pages — sequential read at 3 GB/s is ~5 s for 14 GB; or
#   (b) load weights with explicit ReadFile into owned buffers instead of demand-paged
#       MapViewOfFile (avoid the on-demand fault path entirely); or
#   (c) investigate the specific MapViewOfFile demand-fault stall under this driver
#       (596.21 / CUDA 13.2) — it may be a host page-lock interaction.
# Once the forward completes a full pass reliably, re-run:
#   build-cuda\tests\test_diffjudge_native.exe   (model resident, ~140 forwards, detached)
# and this log auto-fills with per-query picks + final recall@1 / foreign-reject vs 95.6/96.0.
#
# ── MITIGATION ATTEMPTED: full sequential pre-warm — DID NOT UNBLOCK ────────────────
# Added a default-on pre-warm to the harness: read the entire .sp-model sequentially via
# fread once after load (SP_DJ_NOPREWARM=1 to skip), to populate the OS cache before the
# forward's mmap faults. Result:
#   # pre-warm read 14.2 GB in 6.7s        <-- disk is fast (≈2.1 GB/s through fread)
#   # trial 1: P=367 n_tok=623 logits=653MB forward...
#   <still hangs, 0 CPU / 0% GPU>
# AND the OS file cache stayed pinned at ~368 MB the whole time (it did NOT retain the
# 14.2 GB just read, despite 19.7 GB free RAM). So: (1) standby cache is being capped/
# evicted on this box, and (2) MORE IMPORTANTLY the forward STILL deadlocks immediately
# after a proven-fast full read — confirming the hang is in the MapViewOfFile demand-fault
# path itself, NOT mere cold-read latency. A separate-handle pre-read cannot prime the
# mapping's own page state. The real fix must change the loader's residency strategy
# (ReadFile into owned buffers, or PrefetchVirtualMemory on the actual mapped view), which
# is in the math-core loader (sp_model_load.c / arena), outside N4's additive scope.
